Here are both approaches for .NET MAUI Shell navigation:

## 1. The Model

```csharp
public class Product
{
    public string Id { get; set; }
    public string Name { get; set; }
    public decimal Price { get; set; }
}
```

## 2. Navigating (ProductListPage code-behind or VM)

```csharp
// Approach A – pass a simple string ID
await Shell.Current.GoToAsync($"{nameof(ProductDetailsPage)}?productId={product.Id}");

// Approach B – pass the full object via dictionary
await Shell.Current.GoToAsync(nameof(ProductDetailsPage),
    new Dictionary<string, object>
    {
        ["product"] = selectedProduct   // complex object
    });
```

## 3. Receiving with `IQueryAttributable` (ViewModel)

```csharp
public class ProductDetailsViewModel : ObservableObject, IQueryAttributable
{
    private string _productId;
    private Product _product;

    public string ProductId { get => _productId; set => SetProperty(ref _productId, value); }
    public Product Product  { get => _product;  set => SetProperty(ref _product, value); }

    public void ApplyQueryAttributes(IDictionary<string, object> query)
    {
        // Approach A – simple string parameter
        if (query.TryGetValue("productId", out var id))
        {
            ProductId = id.ToString();
            // fetch full product from a service, cache, etc.
        }

        // Approach B – full object (passed via dictionary overload)
        if (query.TryGetValue("product", out var obj) && obj is Product p)
        {
            Product = p;
            ProductId = p.Id;
        }
    }
}
```

## 4. Wire it up

**Register the route and page:**
```csharp
// In AppShell.xaml.cs or MauiProgram.cs
Routing.RegisterRoute(nameof(ProductDetailsPage), typeof(ProductDetailsPage));

// In MauiProgram.cs – register DI
builder.Services.AddTransient<ProductDetailsPage>();
builder.Services.AddTransient<ProductDetailsViewModel>();
```

**Set the BindingContext on the target page:**
```csharp
public partial class ProductDetailsPage : ContentPage
{
    public ProductDetailsPage(ProductDetailsViewModel vm)
    {
        InitializeComponent();
        BindingContext = vm;
    }
}
```

## Key differences

| | String param (`?key=val`) | Dictionary (object) |
|---|---|---|
| **Serialization** | URL-encoded automatically | Passed by reference, no serialization |
| **Supports complex types** | No — strings/primitives only | Yes |
| **Deep-link / URI friendly** | Yes | No |
| **Received as** | `object` (string at runtime) | Original CLR type |

**Rule of thumb:** use the query-string style for simple IDs and deep links; use the dictionary overload when you already have the object in memory and want to avoid a redundant lookup.
